SIMPLE: skiver
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skiver
<hw>Skiv"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Skewer</er>,
<er>Shiver</er> a fragment.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An inferior quality
of leather, made of split sheepskin, tanned by immersion in sumac, and
dyed. It is used for hat linings, pocketbooks, bookbinding,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The cutting tool or machine used in splitting
leather or skins, as sheepskins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skiving</ent>⟦br⟧
